      (1869, 26, 8, 0, N'19A Fortuna', N'Auraxis Firearms launched the Fortuna Mercenary for the discerning soldier of fortune that prefers close-quarters combat without having to give up their shotgun.', 2, 1, 79745),
      (1879, 26, 6, 0, N'NC6A GODSAW', N'Co-developed with Genudine''s Offense Development team, the NC6A GODSAW incorporates an alternate firing mode which allows the weapon to pierce heavy armor in exchange for reduced infantry damage.', 2, 1, 79748),
      (1884, 26, 4, 0, N'The Brawler', N'Exemplary of NC ingenuity and their utter disdain for rules, the aftermarket parts welded into the Brawler not only make it more accurate than typical shotguns, but also illegal to possess in the Terran Republic. Not that they care.', 2, 1, 79760),
      (1889, 26, 3, 0, N'The Executive', N'The Auraxium variant of the NC4, The Executive is typically only issued to the enigmatic members of The Board, the New Conglomerate''s governing body. It features a unique low-velocity suppressor that doesn''t affect stopping power at range.', 2, 1, 79751),
      (1894, 26, 6, 0, N'Betelgeuse 54-A', N'Orion''s largest star also shines brightly as a powerful, accurate LMG capable of sustained suppressing fire. Plagued by multiple redesigns during its troubled development, the third and final iteration proved itself as a favorite amongst the VS.', 1, 1, 79799),
      (1899, 26, 5, 0, N'Tempest ', N'Custom-built for Sigma Squad''s infamous Hossin Rebirth mission, the unique Tempest SMG performs similar as a carbine at long distances.', 2, 1, 79754),
      (1904, 26, 7, 0, N'T1A Unity', N'The TR released the Unity to commemorate the time-tested Cycler assault rifle, a key weapon attributed to helping bring Earth together under the Terran Republic''s harmonious rule.', 3, 1, 79766),
      (1909, 26, 7, 0, N'Darkstar', N'Built off of the Pulsar assault rifle, the long-range Darkstar was named after the notorious squad of designated marksman medics that popularized its use.', 1, 1, 79793),
      (1914, 26, 8, 0, N'TRAC-Shot', N'Though not officially sanctioned for use on the field, the TR has turned a blind eye to the use of the TRAC-Shot. Bolted together by TR mechanics in their downtime, the TRAC-Shot''s multiple rail attachments are unconventional but effective.', 3, 1, 79769),
      (1919, 26, 8, 0, N'Eclipse VE3A', N'The Eclipse easily overshadows its predecessor, the Solstice, as a close-quarters combat king. It comes equipped with an underbarrel plasma shotgun for ambushes and last-ditch scenarios.', 1, 1, 79796),
      (1924, 26, 6, 0, N'T9A "Butcher"', N'The Butcher gained its reputation as a fearsome weapon capable of unending, long-range suppressive fire following a series of extended engagements at The Crown. Built on the CARV platform, the Butcher''s notoriety has been earned over time in blood.', 3, 1, 79772),
      (1934, 26, 4, 0, N'Havoc', N'The TR''s infamous Havoc Squad popularized this shotgun loadout enough to have it put into production. Primarily used with behind-the-lines galaxy drops to secure CCs, the Havoc can clear rooms and hold points with the best of them.', 3, 1, 79784),
      (1939, 26, 4, 0, N'Chaos', N'Named for the pandemonium this highly modified plasma-core shotgun can cause in a surprise ambush, the Chaos'' reputation as a very deadly flanking weapon has been well earned.', 1, 1, 79790),
      (1944, 26, 5, 0, N'Shuriken', N'Designed for use by the Terran Republic''s top Infiltrator hit squads, the Shuriken''s incredible flexibility both close-up and at a distance allowed TR assassins to deal with a multitude of situations they may''ve not survived otherwise.', 3, 1, 79778),
      (1949, 26, 5, 0, N'Skorpios', N'The Skorpios was created as an outdoor SMG to bolster the survivability of the Vanu Sovereignty''s frightening Wraith squads when their cloaked Flashes were past running condition.', 1, 1, 79805),
      (1954, 26, 3, 0, N'The President', N'This Auraxium-clad variant of the TX1 Repeater is a replica of former Terran Republic President Connery''s weapon of choice. Equipped with a special suppressor, this silenced pistol remains effective even at longer ranges.', 3, 1, 79775),
      (1959, 26, 3, 0, N'The Immortal', N'Commissioned by the undying founder of the Vanu Sovereignty for use as his own personal sidearm, Briggs'' variant of the Beamer, The Immortal, features an integrated suppressor that retains stopping power even at a distance.', 1, 1, 79802),
      (1964, 26, 13, 0, N'The Kraken', N'Nanite Systems'' mightiest anti-tank weapon received a facelift with the release of The Kraken, a commemorative Auraxium-plated Decimator. Its powerful warheads create a miniaturized singularity upon impact.', 0, 1, 85785),
